description: This file defines data models representing API entities such as User, Job, Application, Company, and Messaging structures. It includes class definitions with JSON serialization factory methods.

classes.name: UserProfile
classes.description: Represents a user profile with id, name, email, optional avatar URL, bio, and phone.

classes.name: Job
classes.description: Represents a job listing with details such as title, company, location, description, salary, and application status.

classes.name: JobApplication
classes.description: Represents a user's application for a job, with id, job id, and status.

classes.name: Company
classes.description: Represents a company with id, name, and optional about information.

classes.name: MessageThread
classes.description: Represents a message thread with contact name, list of messages, and related metadata.

classes.name: Message
classes.description: Represents a message with sender, text content, and timestamp.

methods.name: UserProfile.fromJson
methods.description: Factory method to create a UserProfile instance from a JSON map.

methods.name: Job.fromJson
methods.description: Factory method to create a Job instance from a JSON map.

methods.description: Factory method to create a JobApplication instance from a JSON map.

methods.name: Company.fromJson
methods.description: Factory method to create a Company instance from a JSON map.

methods.description: Factory method to create a MessageThread instance from a JSON map.
